Incident.Summary: During the execution of a search warrant, the residence was found to be kept in unsafe conditions for juveniles.

IncidentSuppNarrative.NarrativeText:
Reason for Submission:
CED Initial

Body Worn Camera: My agency issued body worn camera was activated during this incident.

Narrative:

    On September 9, 2023, investigators from the Criminal Enforcement Division Eastern Region executed a search and seizure warrant at 11410 Bratten Avenue, Apartment 18, Princess Anne, Somerset County, Maryland in reference to a separate case.

During the execution of the search warrant, I made contact with the leaseholder and resident identified as Tylisha Sullivan [hereinafter referred to as Sullivan] and her children.
  • Gekhi Sullivan, DOB: 12/4/2009
  • Ny’heim Sullivan, DOB: 8/1/2008
  • Ke’Shaun Sullivan, DOB: 4/19/2013
  • Ge’ ett Cornish, DOB: 11/13/2011
  • Keniyah Harris, DOB: 12/8/2006
  • Tamiyah Sullivan, DOB: 4/28/2016
  • Daryah Hardy, DOB: 7/11/2019

During a search of the residence, investigators located maggots on the floor crawling from decaying food located on the floor, dog feces throughout the apartment and used maxi-pads. The rooms appeared to be in unlivable conditions as mattresses were piled in a bedroom and separate bedroom(s) were laced with clothing. One bedroom was identified as having clothing strung across the floor that were covered in dog feces. The bathtub was located to have approximately 4 inches of standing brown water. There were several holes within the walls creating safety concerns for the small children residing within the residence. Investigators photographed the interior of the residence.





Based on these findings, I submitted a referral through the Somerset County Department of Social Services and requested an investigation be opened for the welfare of the children residing at this location.

On September 22, 2023, I consulted with the Somerset County States Attorney’s Office in reference to charges for child neglect.

An application for charges against Sullivan was submitted to the Somerset County District Court Commissioners Office and a criminal summons was issued for seven (7) counts of child neglect.

Case open, pending summons service.

Reason for Submission:
Criminal Summons Served

Body Worn Camera:  My Body Worn Camera was activated during the interaction.

Narrative:

On October 3, 2023, at approximately 0916hrs, I made contact with Tylisha Sullivan [hereinafter referred to as Sullivan] at her residence listed as 11410 Bratten Avenue, Apt 18, Princess Anne, Maryland.
Sullivan was served the criminal summons for the following charges:

Seven (7) counts of Neglect of Minor

Sullivan advised she had no questions and had already been contacted by DSS.

Case Closed.
